**Key Results** 

- A single injection induced sustained mosquitocidal efficacy for at least two months, achieving HR >4 against both susceptible and resistant Anopheles populations and meeting WHO PPC for malaria endectocides.

- A single long acting injectable IVM campaign achieved 16-29\%, rising to 33-57\%, 48-74\%, and 59-78\% with two, three, and four campaigns, respectively over one year.

- Aedes present a better resistance to IVM than Anopheles 

- Individuals treated with IVM are not more attractive than non treated 

**Impact**  
Central study for the development of a novel malaria control tool that fit WHO recommandations for endectocides efficacy against malaria vector. The results obtained during this study allows the pharmaceutical partner to begin a phase I to test the formulation on human. The confirmation of no behavioral modification is an insurance of the efficacy along time of this molecule and the impact on resistance will be taking into account for deployment strategy and other studies will be done to avoid this treat. 

